<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_R1.1_M_FS_UsageLicence.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_R1.1_M_FS_UsageLicence.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_R1.1_M_FS_UsageLicence.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_R1.1_M_FS_UsageLicence.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - R1.1 - resource declares a usage licence"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_R1.1_M_FS_UsageLicence"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_R1.1_M_FS_UsageLicence"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the FAIRsharing database, standard or policy record declares at least one usage licence. This metric is based on the FAIRsharing operationalisation that evaluates the presence of one or more licences associated with the resource. The assessment expects the FAIRsharing DOI or URL of the record under evaluation and retrieves the corresponding FAIRsharing metadata to evaluate the usage licence information recorded for the resource.

**Why should we measure it?**

R1.1 requires that (meta)data are released with a clear and accessible usage licence. Declaring a usage licence allows users and assessment services to determine the conditions under which the resource may be accessed, used and reused. This metric evaluates only the presence of licence information and does not assess the suitability or legal content of the licence itself."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:applicationArea <http://www.fairsharing.org/ontology/subject/SRAO_0000401> ;
    ftr:inDimension <https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/R1.1> ;
    dcat:version "1.0.0"^^xsd:string ;
    
    
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
     
    
    
    
    
